<div class="container-fluid">
  <div class="row-fluid row">
    <div class="span2">
      <% if current_user.avatar? %>
        <%= filepicker_image_tag current_user.avatar, w: 75, h: 75, fit: 'crop' %>
      <% else %>
        <img src="//placehold.it/75" class="img-polaroid">
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <div class="span8">
      <div class="page-header">
          <h2>
            Hi <%= current_user.name %>
            <small>This is your promoter administrative area</small>
          </h2>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row-fluid row">
    <div class="span4">
      <h4>Recent Updates</h4>
      <div class="well sidebar-nav-fixed" id="update">
        <ul class="nav nav-list">
          <li class="nav-header">Today's Sales </li>
          <% @sales.each do |s| %>
            <dd><%= link_to "#{s.event.artist}", promoter_event_path(s.event) %> <span class="badge badge pull-right"><%= s.quantity %></span></dd>
          <% end %>
          <li class="divider"></li>
          <li class="nav-header">Unread Tour requests <span class="badge badge-info pull-right"><%= @tour_requests.count %></span></li>
          <% @tour_requests.limit(3).each do |r| %>
          <dd><%= r.user.name %> <%= distance_of_time_in_words_to_now(r.created_at, include_seconds = false) %> ago</dd>
          <% end %>
          <li class="divider"></li>
          <li class="nav-header">Unread Support Requests <span class="badge badge-info pull-right"><%= @support_requests.count %></span></li>
          <% @support_requests.limit(3).each do |r| %>
          <dd><%= r.user.name %> <%= distance_of_time_in_words_to_now(r.created_at, include_seconds = false) %> ago</dd>
          <% end %>
          <li class="divider"></li>
          <li>
            <%= link_to "All Requests >>", requests_path, class: "btn btn-large" %>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div><!--/.well -->
    </div><!--/span-->

    <div class="span8 span-fixed-sidebar">

      <div class="row-fluid">

        <div class="span6">
          <h4>Public Profile</h4>

          <p>Your public profile is where people can view information and statistics about all the shows you have organized. You can edit it in place by clicking on the edit link at the top of your profile. You can also hide or delete your profile at any time, by default your profile is hidden. </p> <br>
          <% if current_user.profile %>
            <p><%= link_to "View >>", promoter_profile_path(current_user.profile), class: "btn btn-primary" %></p>
          <% else %>
            <p><%= link_to "Create your Profile", promoter_profiles_path, method: :post, class: "btn btn-success" %></p>
          <% end %>
        </div><!--/span-->
        <div class="span6">
          <h4>Your Events</h4>
          <p>All your current and past events are listed here. You can edit the event details, including applying on-the-fly ticket discounts (info docs for more) as well as viewing all current tickets sales and customer details. Charges and refunds can also be applied in this section, either in bulk or isolation. </p>
          <p><%= link_to "View >>", promoter_events_path, class: "btn btn-primary" %></p>
        </div>
        <br>
      <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span6">
          <h4>Payments</h4>
          <p>In order to receive sales monies into your bank account, you need to connect a Stripe account to your 100 Motels account. After you create a Public Profile you'll see a 'connect with Stripe' button that'll take you to Stripe.com. Fill out the application form or log into your Stripe account and you're done.</p>
          <p><% if current_user.profile && current_user.profile.api_key %>
              <button class="btn btn-success">Connected <i class="icon-ok-circle icon-white"></i></button>
            <% elsif current_user.profile %>
              <%= link_to image_tag('blue.png'), user_omniauth_authorize_path(:stripe_connect), class: "" %>
            <% end %></p>
        </div><!--/span-->
        <div class="span6">
          <h4>Your Account</h4>
          <p>This is your normal user account where you can update or change basic details like your password, primary email etc. If you are also a customer of other 100 Motels promoters you can add or update a credit card here. </p> <br><br>
          <p><%= link_to "View >>", user_path(current_user), class: "btn btn-primary" %></p>
        </div><!--/span-->
      </div>

        </div><!--/span-->
      </div><!--/row-->
    </div><!--/span-->
  </div><!--/row-->

  <hr>

</div><!--/.fluid-container-->â€‹